        "title": "Public Cloud",
        "content": "The Public Cloud model offers resources owned and operated by a third-party provider, making them available to multiple tenants.\n\n*   **Multi-tenancy:** Resources are shared among different users or organizations.\n*   **Cost-Effective:** Pay-as-you-go pricing model reduces capital expenditure.\n*   **Scalability:** Easily scale resources up or down based on demand.\n*   **Examples:** AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform."
      },
      {
        "title": "Private Cloud",
        "content": "The Private Cloud model provides infrastructure exclusively for a single organization.\n\n*   **Single-tenancy:** Resources are dedicated to one organization.\n*   **Enhanced Security:** Greater control over data and security measures.\n*   **Customization:** Tailored to meet specific business requirements.\n*   **Deployment Options:** Can be hosted on-premises or by a third-party provider."
      },
      {
        "title": "Hybrid Cloud",
        "content": "The Hybrid Cloud model combines Public and Private Cloud infrastructures, allowing data and applications to be shared between them.\n\n*   **Flexibility:** Choose the best environment for each workload.\n*   **Scalability:** Leverage public cloud resources for peak demands.\n*   **Compliance:** Keep sensitive data in a private cloud while utilizing public cloud for other applications.\n*   **Cost Optimization:** Balance costs by using the most appropriate cloud environment."
      }
    ]
  }
}
